That the Riches of this World are not our Happineſs;
                  2. and that when Men look on them as felicitating things, they ſet their Eyes on that which is not. They are not the Happineſs of our Bodies, much leſs of our Souls. If we were Maſters of both the Indies, we could not buy off one Stab of the Gout, or one twitch of the Collick, or the leaſt Pang of any acute Diſtemper. If an Eye be periſhed, or a Foot Gangren'd, the moſt maſſy Treaſure cannot reſtore the decay'd Part to Perfection;

 or purchaſe a healthy Conſtitution to a crazy and languiſhing Body.
